We‚Äôre excited to announce our reopening plan for the 2020-2021 school year. As is the case with everything we do, the plan is centered on serving our students‚Äô and families‚Äô needs with a specific focus on 3 items: 1. Health and safety 2. Flexibility 3. What‚Äôs best for our students
While our detailed remote learning plan can be found on our website, key highlights of the plan are as follows:
Students have the option to attend in person and there will be three 2-hour sessions to choose from
Students have the option to work 100% from home
Students will have the option to choose a combination of in person and remote instruction

post_text:
Tomorrow (6/23) is the Car Parade for Graduation!

If you are signed up for this event it will be rain or shine.
Come in your cap and gown!!! üòä

Please meet at St. Vincent's parking lot at 1:00 p.m. staff members and police officers will be there to help you line up. Graduates MUST follow the directions the staff gives you. You are only allowed to have one car per graduate, but you can fill up that car with loved ones. All of this is non-negotiable.

When you pull up to the school you do not get out of the car. Mrs. Fraser and Mrs. Caranna will present the diploma to you at your window.

We are trying our best to accommodate all students and staff during this COVID 19 crisis so it is important we follow instructions to the best of our ability.

Can't wait to celebrate! üéâ

post_text:
IMPORTANT INFORMATION FOR SENIORS FROM THE OHIO DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION.
Students are eligible for local graduation flexibility, but not necessarily entitled to graduate. The determination of whether a student is ‚Äúon track to graduate‚Äù is determined locally.

What this means is, it is the school's decision as to who is eligible for graduation flexibility. Seniors at Towpath Trail High School who choose not to continue to complete their school work during the closure will NOT be considered "on track" and will not receive a diploma. Students who want to graduate this year MUST continue to make efforts to engage with their school work and make good faith attempts to complete as many of their remaining classes as possible.

I was able to pick up the mail today and there were four packets of work. Students-most of you received return envelopes for your work with your packets. Please start mailing your work back to us! I will pick the mail up every Monday on my way to packet pick up/drop off at the school.

You can also take pictures of your assignments and send them to your teachers through email or text (if they've shared their phone number).

You can drop packets off at the school between 12-2 on Mondays.

There are multiple ways to turn your work in, so please be sure to start sending those packets of completed work back ASAP!

I want to recognize Timmea, Diamond D., London M., Ray and Evajeh for returning your packets! I am grading your work now, so you should see updated grades in Apex by the end of the day!

Students- if you get a packet of work in the mail with no return envelope, you can either:
1. Hold on to it until school resumes.
2. Drop it off on Monday, April 6th at the school between 12-2 p.m.
3. Take pictures of your work and email them to a teacher to grade.
4. Wait for your next packet -there will be a return envelope in it and mail it back.

Envelope's are scarce and on back order. Please be patient as we are all trying to navigate this the best way we can considering the circumstances.

post_text: Due to the Governor's shelter in place order, Towpath Trail High School will be unoccupied from Tuesday, March 24-Sunday, April 5. Teachers and staff will still be available by email for any questions you have concerning your school work or if you have any other needs. You can also send us a message on this page if you have a question. Rest assured, we will all be working from home to ensure that all of you have access to your school work. Please remember that we are all doing the very best we can do with what we have right now. Your patience and understanding is appreciated.

While we all would like to know what is going forward with the rest of the school year, Towpath Trail High School Staff is still unaware of what lies ahead.
Parents and Students, please take the time to read this article as it explains a bit more detail of our pending status.

Please feel free to reach out on Facebook, call the school or email your teachers if you have any further questions. At this time, we are still on a three week closure.

Stay safe, wash your hands, practice social distancing and work on those classes!

CLEVELAND.COM
Coronavirus school closure will be longer, but graduation not in jeopardy, say DeWine and State Supt. DeMaria

March 10, 2020
Dear Families:
Student safety and wellness is our highest priority. Today, the administrative team and I conferred to review processes, procedures, and protocols related to the Coronavirus (COVID-19). The number of cases in the U.S. and the immediate health risk from COVID-19 remains low at this time. Yet, the current global circumstances suggest that there is a high possibility this virus may continue to spread and may eventually impact our schools and communities at large. With student safety as a top priority, we are proactively monitoring this situation with health officials.
Our best defense against the spread of respiratory viruses, including the coronavirus and‚Ä¶ More
